Description: We provide you a platform to implement fast, private, cost-effective, and efficient deep learning applications on edge devices.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Deep Force believes that in the near future the currently cloud dominant intelligence will shift towards the edge. This shift towards smart edge devices will bring many improvements such as improved privacy, lower latency, reduced bandwidth usage, and more efficient storage.  Recently, many businesses are actively trying to implement deep learning to reap the benefits mentioned above, yet they have encountered many challenges in the adoption of smart AI solutions into their existing products. These challenges include a lack of in-house AI experts, hardware computational power / cost limitations, and time to market pressures, just name a few.   At Deep Force, we understand the struggle businesses face and seek to empower companies to quickly adopt Deep Learning by creating optimized AI modules that are hardware independent. This allows companies to quickly implement smart features into existing hardware without the need to hire additional experts to create novel algorithms.

Description: Pressure Analysis Company (PAC) designs and manufactures wireless impact sensors that detect and track direct impacts
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Pressure Analysis Company (PAC) designs and manufactures wireless impact sensors that detect and track direct impacts with the highest sensitivity and accuracy. PAC holds the exclusive option to license the technology developed by University of New Mexico researcher and PAC team member Dr. Scott S. Sibbett. Their sensors are proven to be more sensitive and accurate than other accelerometer-based sensors during a series of tests at Los Alamos National Laboratory. In August 2015 the team completed the ABQid business accelerator program and is developing prototypes that will be tested on the field. PAC was founded in 2013 as an S-Corporation.  Their first product, SmackCAP Athlytics™, is a skullcap for athletes in contact sports that tracks every hit, every time. When an athlete is hit, the impact data is wirelessly transmitted to sideline staff in real time via our mobile application. The data is also stored in the cloud, so an ImPACt Scorecard™ can be made available to athletes and their doctors as an added layer of information to assess risks, performance levels, and technique.
